quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  106,1,"For the accustomed security of the Quraysh<sup>1</sup>,","[1] Allah had given Quraysh the honor of being guardians of the Holy Ka‘bah, which allowed them to travel in peace without fear of being harmed."
  106,2,"secure in their winter and summer journeys<sup>2</sup>.","[2] i.e., their trading caravans would travel south to Yemen in winter and north to the Levant in summer."
  106,3,"Let them worship the Lord of this [Sacred] House<sup>3</sup>,","[3] i.e., the Ka‘bah."
  106,4,"Who fed them against hunger and made them secure against fear<sup>4</sup>.","[4] The people of Quraysh were blessed with provision and security probably because of the prayer of Abraham. See 14:35-37"
  107,1,"Have you seen the one who denies the Recompense?",""
  107,2,"Such is the one who repulses the orphan harshly,",""
  107,3,"and does not urge others to feed the needy.",""
  107,4,"So woe to those who pray,",""
  107,5,"but are heedless of their prayer<sup>1</sup>;","[1] i.e., the hypocrites who do not pray except to show off and others who are heedless to pray at their specified times."
  107,6,"those who only show off,",""
  107,7,"and withhold even the small kindnesses.",""
  108,1,"We have surely given you [O Prophet] al-Kauthar [i.e., abundance]<sup>1</sup>,","[1] i.e., abundance, of which is the river of al-Kauthar in Paradise."
  108,2,"so pray and offer sacrifice to your Lord alone.",""
  108,3,"Indeed, the one who hates you is truly cut off [from all goodness]<sup>2</sup>.","[2] Both in this world and in the Hereafter."
